# QuestCore — single folder (junctions)

## Source of truth

`D:\Games\World of Warcraft\_retail_\Interface\AddOns\QuestCore`

The following paths are **directory junctions** to the same folder (do not copy or sync):

- `D:\Games\World of Warcraft\_anniversary_\Interface\AddOns\QuestCore` (TBC)
- `D:\Games\World of Warcraft\_classic_\Interface\AddOns\QuestCore` (Mists)
- `D:\Games\World of Warcraft\_classic_era_\Interface\AddOns\QuestCore` (Classic Era)

**Edit only under retail.** Changes appear in all clients automatically.

Do **not** run `Sync-Clients.ps1`, robocopy, or mirror edits to other paths.

Reference only (do not modify): sibling guide reference addon in the same AddOns folder.

## Backups (optional cleanup)

Pre-junction copies were kept as `QuestCore.pre-junction-backup` in each client's AddOns folder. Safe to delete once you confirm everything works.

## Restore junctions (if broken)

From PowerShell, after removing a broken `QuestCore` folder:

```powershell
New-Item -ItemType Junction -Path "D:\Games\World of Warcraft\_anniversary_\Interface\AddOns\QuestCore" -Target "D:\Games\World of Warcraft\_retail_\Interface\AddOns\QuestCore"
```

(Repeat for `_classic_` and `_classic_era_`.)
